A FAST-growing brokerage firm providing trading solutions for investment financial markets, Tradelandfx, has said it will create 500 jobs for youths this year and 2,000 by 2024. The firm said the jobs will include introductory broker, full-time employee, expert trader, copy trader or partner. Human Resource Manager of Tradelandfx Chukwuma Amanambu said the firm is aware of the unemployment rate, which is 33 per cent. He said the firm would build a pathway for financial freedom for Nigerians and Africans.   Lagos Cooperative College to graduate 104     Court affirms expiration of farmers association exco     Cleric makes case for service   Tradeland FX Business Director Amarachi Ihedirimadu explained the rationale for opening an office in Abuja. She said: “We have come to create a trading platform for beginners and advanced traders to access the financial market, we offer free weekly training because we understand knowledge is an important investment one can have. “You can open an account with us with as little as $1 and it comes  fully packed with educational materials.” Firm’s Marketing Manager  Amarachi Ugwuegbulam said the firm as part of its marketing campaign, will be having a trading contest where both new and existing customers will be credited $100,000. She said: “They will be trading for a period of one month, at the end of the trading period, the winners will be getting $5,000 to $1,500.”